<!--Telling readers why they should go here-->
<h2> Why should you go? </h2>
	<p><b>The Acropolis of Athens is a beautiful ancient citadel
	located in Athens, Greece. It's an amazing site to see with your <br /> friends or family and
	would be an amazing experience. The Acropolis is a very interesting piece <br />
	of history. There is also more than the Acropolis to visit in Athens.</b></p>
<!-- More information about the acropolis-->
<h2> More Information </h2>
	<p>To enter the Acropolis it costs 10-20 Euros (depending on the time of year) which <br />
	is 12-24 dollars in us dollars.The Acropolis is home to one of the most famous <br />
	buildings in the world, the Parthenon. The Acropolis is 490 feet tall and has <br />
	a surface area of approximately 7 acres! </p>
